Architecture: any
Depends: +ACQAew-shlibs:Depends+AH0-, +ACQAew-misc:Depends+AH0-
Description: peer-to-peer network based digital currency - Qt GUI
 BitCore is an experimental new digital currency that enables instant
 payments to anyone, anywhere in the world. BitCore uses peer-to-peer
 technology to operate with no central authority: managing transactions
 and issuing money are carried out collectively by the network. BitCore Core
 is the name of the open source software which enables the use of this currency.
 .
 This package provides BitCore-Qt, a GUI for BitCore based on Qt.

Package: bitcore-tx
Architecture: any
Depends: +ACQAew-shlibs:Depends+AH0-, +ACQAew-misc:Depends+AH0-
Description: peer-to-peer digital currency - standalone transaction tool
 BitCore is an experimental new digital currency that enables instant
 payments to anyone, anywhere in the world. BitCore uses peer-to-peer
 technology to operate with no central authority: managing transactions
 and issuing money are carried out collectively by the network. BitCore Core
 is the name of the open source software which enables the use of this currency.
 .
 This package provides bitcore-tx, a command-line transaction creation
 tool which can be used without a bitcore daemon.  Some means of
 exchanging minimal transaction data with peers is still required.
